  "text": "3.4. Tightness of X \u01eb and regularity of X . In this section, we prove that the convergence in law of X \u01eb towards X given by proposition 3.2 holds in a functional sense and that the field X is locally H\u00f6lderian. The straight way to do so is to prove the tightness of the sequence X \u01eb by means of a Kolmogorov estimate (cf. chapter 13 of [CITATION_1] ). Then there exists \u01eb 0 > 0 and C independent of \u01eb such that for \u01eb < \u01eb 0 and |h| R:",
